important cells in our brain.

00:53:59.670 --> 00:54:01.270 align:middle line:84%
And again, we tend
to always think

00:54:01.270 --> 00:54:05.336 align:middle line:84%
about neurons--
this is well known

00:54:05.336 --> 00:54:07.960 align:middle line:84%
in the scientific community, but
not in the general community--

00:54:07.960 --> 00:54:11.470 align:middle line:84%
that these glial cells,
these are living creatures

00:54:11.470 --> 00:54:14.470 align:middle line:84%
that we want to respect,
and nurture, and encourage

00:54:14.470 --> 00:54:15.890 align:middle line:90%
their growth and development.

00:54:15.890 --> 00:54:18.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do we
get more glial cells?

00:54:18.280 --> 00:54:20.470 align:middle line:84%
>>WALDMAN: These types
of meditation exercises,

00:54:20.470 --> 00:54:22.930 align:middle line:84%
